hat do we want?

A society of the people needs to ask this question continuously. 

What do we want?

Freedom is the primary  answer from 1776. Security as national defense serves in service of freedom. 

Leave us alone is the Republican ideal. Being unfettered is also the Anarchist and Libertarian ideal. 

However does freedom mean the same thing in 2025 as it did in 1776? 

No. Today we are dependent far more than 1776. No individual can build a car, a house, or pretty much anything modern we depend on today. 

Freedom rings hollow in such a dependent society.

So what do we want?

We want quality of life. We want modern transportation, education and technology. 

We must recognize then that our lives will require group effort and time in exchange for this quality.

Our society was not designed for quality. It was designed for "leave us alone" freedom with the bare minimum of group mandated dependency.

Republican culture war is anchored on leave us alone. They want a society of might makes right. Slavery, misogyny, child marriage, child labor and gambling are not the concerns of the government. We are free, no DEI.

What do we the people want.

Let's do a thought exercise. Let's advance one billion years into the future. Humans have indefinite lifespans. We are forever young. We are all genetically engineered to be disease resistant, high intelligence, and highly athletic. 

What would these people of the future want?

All the technology of this future would make us even more dependent on each other? Would this be too stifling? Would we lose all freedom?

What we want then is control. We want control over our lives even as we submit to group control for technological benefits.

Freedom then is no longer the root password to society. The new password is control. 

An immediate corollary of this is that rights which demarcate freedom boundaries are replaced by responsibilities. There are no rights in a billion years, only responsibilities that require work. This work defines domains of quality of life balanced with control.

There is one other aspect of our billion year future society that we need to consider: human limitations.

So much of society today treats human nature as immutable. This is false. The entire Trans debate is a war between fixed, immutable human nature factions versus human nature is ours to change.

A billion years from now we will have learned 100% genetic manipulation. We will ensure every newborn is as close to ideal as we can muster.

Religion then is dead. Religion only applies in fixed human nature society.

What we are seeing today is religion fighting to maintain its privilege afforded it by static nature.

What we want then is control. That control includes complete control over human nature. Religion must be annihilated. 

Control must necessarily be a balance between self control, what we call freedom today, and group control. Further this balance must itself be controlled by a design.

Hands off government is not a design of balanced control. So Democracy so designed is not what we want. Call such Democracy Old Democracy.

New Democracy is a society designed with explicit control boundaries.

What do we want?

We can lay aside our billion year thought experiment. 

Today we are just getting started with engineering human nature. This means what we the people want must include human nature limitations. Each according to their own gifts of nature, and limitations of nature.

The future will be an incremental march towards pure will for us individually and as groups. This is a result of removing natural limitations as well as controlling the capabilities we want rather than accidents of birth.

This means the design of our control society needs to constantly change with human nature engineering capabilities to remove limitations like aging as well as add capabilities like sex changes.

The last piece of our control design is to acknowledge natural limitations we cannot control. First and foremost is we can never control for all the variables at large scale. This means that even a trillion years from now we will still need to rely on experiments as total control is not physically possible due to complexity.

What do we want?

We want an experimental society that provides a designed control balance between the individual and society. 

This design is called Irreni World Scale. The campaign today is called New Democracy.

Thomas Jefferson quipped that the government that governs best governs least because the society governs itself. New Democracy takes this notion one step further and eliminates government altogether. This is because hierarchies of top down control do not balance control for everyone, only those at the top of the hierarchy 

